    "body": "This PR suggests a conservative approach to fix the problem.\r\n\r\nWe could later refine it using an ignore list (we ignore a specific set of directives) or using a list of directives we know modify the code while considering the others do not.\r\n\r\nMeant to fix #7532.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [],
    "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/cython/cython/issues/7539/comments",
    "commit_data": [
        {
            "author": null,
            "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/cython/cython/commits/2e9246677bb9ea24f6dccee05d7e5f7e9ad9a927/comments",
            "commit": {
                "author": {
                    "date": "2026-02-22T10:45:41Z",
                    "email": "v01dxyz@v01d.xyz",
                    "name": "v01dxyz"
                },
                "comment_count": 0,
                "committer": {
                    "date": "2026-02-22T11:07:52Z",
                    "email": "v01dxyz@v01d.xyz",
                    "name": "v01dxyz"
                },
                "message": "Fix cache ignoring `compiler_directives` when fingerprinting compiler options\n\nSome compiler_directives influence the generated C code. It is the\ncase with the ones for profiling/tracing (profiling, linetrace) that\nadd instrumentation code.\n\nTaking them into account when computing the cache key allows the user\nto really have a debug version and correctly get profiling/coverage\nreports. And the way round, the user won't ship a debug version\ninstead of a release one. Otherwise, it would silently fail.\n\nGH-issue: [BUG] Cache fingerprinting ignores `compiler_directives` #7532",
                "tree": {
                    "sha": "d0cc28f29ecf64df39cfaedfbc4844b255e1d3dc",
                    "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/cython/cython/git/trees/d0cc28f29ecf64df39cfaedfbc4844b255e1d3dc"
                },
